Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['pɔrindʒə]
*danh từ
 ■bát ăn cháo, tô ăn cháo

Anh - Anh
porringer
['pɒrɪn(d)ʒə]
■ noun historical a small bowl, often with a handle, used for soup or similar dishes.
Origin
ME (earlier as potager and pottinger): from OFr. potager, from potage 'contents of a pot'.
